# CODEX_HOME points here (~/.config/codex), and stow symlinks this directory into
# place — so Codex writes ALL of its runtime state into this folder: credentials
# (auth.json — an API token!), session history, logs, caches, lockfiles, installed
# plugins. Fail closed: ignore everything, then re-include only the hand-authored
# config. A new state file Codex invents tomorrow is ignored by default, not leaked.
*

!.gitignore
!config.toml
!AGENTS.md
!rules/
!rules/**
!hooks/
!hooks/**
